data.description:
Welcome to 144 Bosarvey Drive, Ormond Beach, Florida--a charming residence that beckons qualified buyers with an enticing assumable loan interest rate of 4.625%. Elevate your living experience in this beachside abode boasting 4 bedrooms, 3 bathrooms, and a host of desirable features.Step inside to discover the allure of original hardwood floors in the open living room. On the main floor, two bedrooms share a full bathroom, each providing ample closet space and picturesque views. The kitchen splashes between the living room and sunroom, offering backyard vistas and flooded with natural light - and convenient access to the laundry room--a space complete with a shower, vanity sink, and entry to a third bedroom. Ascend to the second floor to find the master bedroom, featuring three closets and a private bathroom. 

Beyond the interior, revel in the resort-style splendor of a sparkling pool complete with a slide, and outdoor shower. The patio beckons with ample space for entertaining, complemented by an outdoor fire pit that enhances the overall outdoor living experience.

This family-friendly haven is further enriched by a 2018 Ondura Roof rated to 130MPH, an HVAC system installed in 2018 with new ducts, an ionizer purification system, a new saltwater pool system added in 2023, and an irrigation system utilizing reclaimed wateradding substantial value to this meticulously maintained residence.

Conveniently situated within a short walk or bike ride to the beach, restaurants, shopping, Publix, the casements, and the bus stop, this home invites you to savor the vibrant lifestyle of Downtown Ormond Beach. Explore the possibilities of making this well-kept family home yours by calling the listing agent today for a personalized tour.

So whether you desire to live in paradise and call this home, or looking to purchase a second and vacation home in one of the greatest beach communities - this property is a must-see!!!

Square footage details sourced from tax rolls. While every effort is made to ensure accuracy, all information recorded in the MLS is intended to be reliable but cannot be guaranteed.
